UNHCR and MSF withdraw from hotspots describing them as prisons
Both the UN refugee agency (UNHCR) and the Doctors Without Borders (MSF) decided to withdraw from the so-called hotspots on the Greek islands as they say that after the new refugee deal between the EU and Turkey they have been turned into detention faculties.
